 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
	<p>
	This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the 
		representation of text which consists of content and markup and may be structured. 
		The representation may conform to a template or to an externally defined standard. 
		The content may be human interpretable text.  A structure is provided
		to allow items in the content to be directly referenced. The structure is a directed graph.  Each leaf element in the graph
		consists of content and markup.  Content and markup are limited to items that may be
		represented using <express_ref linkend="foundation_representation:arm:Foundation_representation_arm.String_representation_item"/>.
		Content may be explicit or may be an external reference.
	   </p>
 </purpose>

